Ahmad ibn Hanbal al-Dhuhli (Arabic: أَحْمَد بْن حَنْبَل الذهلي, romanized: Aḥmad ibn Ḥanbal al-Dhuhlī; November 780 – 2 August 855 CE/164–241 AH), bụ onye Alakụba, onye ọka iwu, onye na-ekpe ikpe
omenala, na onye nchoputa nke Hanbali ụlọ akwụkwọ nke Sunni jurisprudence - otu n'ime anọ isi n'ụlọ akwụkwọ iwu okpukpe nke Sunni Islam.
